king: _readThinking: .txtThinking: .Thinking:  FirstThinking: ,Thinking:  listThinking:  filesThinking:  toThinking:  seeThinking:  pathThinking: .\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"tool_calls\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"fc_5ec2ef4e-9556-4f9f-9569-f698d18af034\",\n          \"type\": \"function\",\n          \"function\": {\n            \"index\": 0,\n            \"name\": \"read_file\",\n            \"arguments\": \"{\\\"line_from\\\":1,\\\"line_to\\\":200,\\\"path\\\":\\\"/home/babak/workspace/rust/babak_code/to_read.txt\\\"}\"\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"tool\",\n      \"content\": \"content of this file should be returned as they are\",\n      \"tool_call_id\": \"fc_5ec2ef4e-9556-4f9f-9569-f698d18af034\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"Thinking: WeThinking:  haveThinking:  toThinking:  readThinking:  contentsThinking:  ofThinking:  toThinking: _readThinking: .txtThinking: .Thinking:  UseThinking:  readThinking: _fileThinking:  toolThinking: .\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"read contents of AGENTS.md file and propose changes that makes it better\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"tool_calls\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"fc_be1f15fc-1fe1-4aec-acfd-49e8512f5d7d\",\n          \"type\": \"function\",\n          \"function\": {\n            \"index\": 0,\n            \"name\": \"read_file\",\n            \"arguments\": \"{\\\"line_from\\\":1,\\\"line_to\\\":200,\\\"path\\\":\\\"/home/babak/workspace/rust/babak_code/AGENTS.md\\\"}\"\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"tool\",\n      \"content\": \"# babak_code — Agent Instructions\\n\\nA terminal-based AI coding assistant TUI written in Rust (edition 2024).\\nUses `ratatui` + `crossterm` for rendering and `tokio` for async.\\nThe primary purpose is to assist in software development using multiple LLM backends simultaneously or in sequence.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Build & Run\\n\\n```bash\\ncargo build\\ncargo run          # launches the TUI — requires Ollama at localhost:11434\\ncargo test         # run all tests\\ncargo test <name>  # run a single test\\n```\\n\\nLogs are written to `.data/babak_code.log` (created at startup).\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Architecture — The Law\\n\\nThe architecture is the primary constraint. Every change, feature, or refactor\\nmust respect it. If a clean implementation requires an architectural change,\\n**stop and discuss it first** — do not glue things around the existing structure\\nwithout considering the proper approach.\\n\\n### Module Map\\n\\n```\\nsrc/\\n├── main.rs           — bootstrap: terminal setup, logging init\\n├── app.rs            — event loop, wires all modules together\\n│\\n├── models/           — SHARED DATA CONTRACTS (no logic, no I/O)\\n│   ├── model.rs      — LLMModel trait, ChatMessageResponse, request/response types\\n│   ├── thread.rs     — Thread, ContextItem (conversation history)\\n│   └── tool.rs       — Tool, ToolCallRequest, ToolCallResponse, ToolFunction\\n│\\n├── agent/            — LLM BACKEND IMPLEMENTATIONS\\n│   ├── ollama/       — Ollama HTTP backend\\n│   └── groq/         — Groq HTTP backend\\n│\\n├── tool/             — TOOL DEFINITIONS & EXECUTION\\n│   ├── mod.rs        — execute_tool dispatcher, tools_catalog\\n│   ├── file.rs       — read, create, edit, list_files tools\\n│   └── search.rs     — fd_search, rg_search tools\\n│\\n├── controller.rs     — MessageController: conversation state + model registry\\n├── system_prompt/    — system prompt generation (injects tool catalog + AGENTS.md)\\n│\\n├── ui.rs             — display controllers (no conversation state)\\n├── prompt.rs         — ContentManager: multi-line text buffer + history\\n│\\n├── components/       — REUSABLE UI WIDGETS (stateless or self-contained)\\n│   ├── markdown.rs   — markdown → ratatui Text renderer\\n│   ├── text_area.rs  — block-cursor TextArea widget\\n│   └── prompt_dialog.rs — floating modal dialog (schema-driven)\\n│\\n└── service/          — SYSTEM SERVICES\\n    ├── commands/     — slash-command controller and command types\\n    └── system_call.rs — NvidiaSmi GPU monitor\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Module Responsibilities & Boundaries\\n\\n### `models/` — Pure Data Contracts\\nShared types only. **No HTTP, no file I/O, no business logic.**\\n`Thread` and `ContextItem` are dumb data bags — they hold conversation history\\nand nothing else. They must not know about specific model names, tool lists,\\nor request formats. Any conversion to a backend-specific request format belongs\\nin the `agent/` module, not here.\\n\\n> ⚠\u{fe0f} **Known violation to fix:** `thread.rs` currently contains\\n> `impl Into<UserChatMessageRequest> for &Thread` which hardcodes a model name\\n> and tool list. This must be moved into each `LLMModel` impl. Do not copy or\\n> extend this pattern — fix it when touching either file.\\n\\n### `agent/` — LLM Backend Implementations\\nEach subdirectory is one backend (Ollama, Groq, etc.). Each implements the\\n`LLMModel` trait from `models/model.rs`. The backend owns:\\n- The HTTP endpoint and auth (API keys read from environment variables)\\n- Request construction (building `UserChatMessageRequest` from a `Thread`)\\n- Response streaming (parsing newline-delimited JSON → `ChatMessageResponse` tokens)\\n- Tool call serialization for its specific wire format\\n\\nBackends are **isolated from each other**. Adding a new backend means adding a\\nnew subdirectory under `agent/` — nothing else changes.\\n\\n### `LLMModel` Trait Contract\\n\\n```rust\\n#[async_trait]\\npub trait LLMModel {\\n    fn name(&self) -> &str;\\n    fn version(&self) -> &str;\\n    async fn generate(\\n        &self,\\n        thread: &Thread,\\n        tools: &[Tool],                          // always passed; ignore if unsupported\\n        resp_tx: broadcast::Sender<ChatMessageResponse>,\\n    );\\n}\\n```\\n\\n> ⚠\u{fe0f} **Known violation:** `generate` currently does not accept a `tools`\\n> parameter. Tools are baked into the `Thread → request` conversion. This must\\n> be corrected — tools are owned by the `tool/` module and passed in by the\\n> controller, not hardcoded anywhere.\\n\\nThe backend decides whether to include `tools` in the outgoing request. If the\\nmodel does not support native tool-calling, it silently ignores the parameter.\\nThe controller is never aware of per-model capabilities.\\n\\n### `tool/` — Tool Registry & Execution\\nSingle source of truth for all tools. Responsibilities:\\n- Define tool schemas (`Tool` structs with JSON schema parameters)\\n- Implement tool execution logic\\n- Export `execute_tool(call: &ToolCallRequest) -> String` dispatcher\\n- Export `tools_catalog() -> Vec<ToolCatalogEntry>` for system prompt injection\\n\\nTools are **global** — they are not owned by or coupled to any specific model.\\nThe controller passes the full tool list (or a configured subset) to `generate`.\\nThe system prompt always receives the full catalog via `system_prompt/`.\\n\\n### `controller.rs` — Conversation Orchestration\\n`MessageController` owns:\\n- The thread list (`Vec<Thread>`) and the active thread index\\n- The model registry (`HashMap<String, Arc<dyn LLMModel>>`) and active model name\\n- All mutations to conversation state (add user message, assistant response, tool calls)\\n- Tool call execution via `handle_tool_calls`\\n- `prepare_call()` — returns a clone of the active thread + a reference to the active model\\n\\nThe controller does **not** own display state. It does not know about scroll\\npositions, rendered text, or UI layout.\\n\\n### `ui.rs` — Display State Only\\n`PromptController`, `ResponseAreaController`, `StatusLineController` own only\\nwhat is needed to render and scroll. They do not hold conversation history.\\nStreaming tokens are appended via `add_to_payload`; consecutive tokens of the\\nsame `MessageKind` are merged to avoid per-token entries.\\n\\n### `service/commands/` — Slash-Command System\\nThis module handles user-typed commands (e.g. `/model groq`, `/new`, `/clear`).\\nCommands are registered with `CommandController` at startup. The prompt area\\ndetects a leading `/` and routes input to the command controller instead of the\\nLLM. Commands mutate `MessageController` or `App` state directly.\\n\\n> ⚠\u{fe0f} **Currently incomplete:** `CommandController` stores commands but routing\\n> from the prompt is not wired up and `CommandType` variants are unused.\\n> Extend this module rather than adding ad-hoc keybindings for meta-operations.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Streaming Architecture\\n\\n`LLMModel::generate` sends individual `ChatMessageResponse` tokens to a\\n`broadcast::Sender<ChatMessageResponse>`. The final chunk carries `done: true`.\\n`App` receives these in the `tokio::select!` loop:\\n\\n1. Non-done content/thinking chunks → forwarded to `ResponseAreaController`\\n2. `tool_calls` chunk → `MessageController::set_tool_calls` → `execute_tool` →\\n   `set_tool_call_response` → new `generate` spawned to continue the conversation\\n3. `done: true` → `MessageController::set_response` records the final assistant turn\\n\\nEach `generate` call is spawned with `tokio::spawn` making it an independent\\nasync unit. This is the foundation for future sub-agent and background task\\nsupport — each agent/sub-agent gets its own spawn + channel pair.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Thread Model\\n\\n`Thread` holds a `Vec<ContextItem>` representing the full conversation history.\\n`ContextItem` encodes one turn: system, user, assistant content, tool request,\\nor tool response. Use the static constructors (`ContextItem::user`,\\n`ContextItem::assistant`, etc.) — never construct the struct directly.\\n\\n**Future direction:** threads will have a `kind` discriminant:\\n- `UserThread` — user-facing, named, switchable via commands\\n- `AgentThread` — programmatic, short-lived, used by sub-agents\\n\\nKeep this in mind when modifying `Thread` or `MessageController`. Do not\\nadd UI-specific fields to `Thread`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Configuration & Secrets\\n\\nAPI keys are read from environment variables at model construction time:\\n- `GROQ_API_KEY` — Groq backend\\n\\n> ⚠\u{fe0f} **Known violation:** the Groq API key is currently hardcoded in `app.rs`.\\n> Move it to `std::env::var(\\\"GROQ_API_KEY\\\")` at the earliest opportunity.\\n\\nA config file (`~/.config/babak_code/config.toml` or `.data/config.toml`) is\\nthe right long-term home for model endpoints, default model selection, and\",\n      \"tool_call_id\": \"fc_be1f15fc-1fe1-4aec-acfd-49e8512f5d7d\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"tools\": [\n    {\n      \"type\": \"function\",\n      \"function\": {\n        \"name\": \"read_file\",\n        \"description\": \"partial file read based on line_from and line_to parameters. keep line_to rather small number so that parts of file needed is fetched. if line_to is greater than file lines, line_from to end of file is returned\",\n        \"parameters\": {\n          \"additionalProperties\": false,\n          \"properties\": {\n            \"line_from\": {\n              \"description\": \"Starting line number to read from\",\n              \"type\": \"integer\"\n            },\n            \"line_to\": {\n              \"description\": \"Ending line number to read to.\",\n              \"type\": \"integer\"\n            },\n            \"path\": {\n              \"description\": \"Path to the file to read\",\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"required\": [\n            \"path\",\n            \"line_from\",\n            \"line_to\"\n          ],\n          \"type\": \"object\"\n        },\n        \"strict\": true\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"function\",\n      \"function\": {\n        \"name\": \"list_files_and_directories\",\n        \"description\": \"List all files and directories in a given directory. directories are shown with \\\"\\\\\\\" at the end of name\",\n        \"parameters\": {\n          \"additionalProperties\": false,\n          \"properties\": {\n            \"path\": {\n              \"description\": \"Path to the directory to list files from\",\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"required\": [\n            \"path\"\n          ],\n          \"type\": \"object\"\n        },\n        \"strict\": true\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"function\",\n      \"function\": {\n        \"name\": \"create_file\",\n        \"description\": \"Create a new file at the given path with the provided content. Parent directories are created automatically if they do not exist. Overwrites the file if it already exists.\",\n        \"parameters\": {\n          \"additionalProperties\": false,\n          \"properties\": {\n            \"content\": {\n              \"description\": \"Full text content to write into the file\",\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            },\n            \"path\": {\n              \"description\": \"Path of the file to create\",\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"required\": [\n            \"path\",\n            \"content\"\n          ],\n          \"type\": \"object\"\n        },\n        \"strict\": true\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"function\",\n      \"function\": {\n        \"name\": \"edit_file\",\n        \"description\": \"Edit an existing file by replacing an exact occurrence of old_text with new_text. old_text must match exactly once in the file — the call fails if it is not found or appears more than once. Use read_file first to obtain the exact text to match.\",\n        \"parameters\": {\n          \"additionalProperties\": false,\n          \"properties\": {\n            \"new_text\": {\n              \"description\": \"Text to replace old_text with\",\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            },\n            \"old_text\": {\n              \"description\": \"Exact text to search for in the file. Must appear exactly once.\",\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            },\n            \"path\": {\n              \"description\": \"Path to the file to edit\",\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"required\": [\n            \"path\",\n            \"old_text\",\n            \"new_text\"\n          ],\n          \"type\": \"object\"\n        },\n        \"strict\": true\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"function\",\n      \"function\": {\n        \"name\": \"fd_search\",\n        \"description\": \"Search for files and directories by name using fd (fd-find). Returns matching paths one per line. Use 'type' to filter: 'f' = files only, 'd' = directories only, 'l' = symlinks only. Omit 'type' to match all entry kinds. Omit 'path' to search from the current working directory.\",\n        \"parameters\": {\n          \"additionalProperties\": false,\n          \"properties\": {\n            \"path\": {\n              \"description\": \"Root directory to search in. Defaults to '.' (current directory)\",\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            },\n            \"pattern\": {\n              \"description\": \"The name pattern to search for (regex)\",\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            },\n            \"type\": {\n              \"description\": \"Entry type filter: 'f' for files, 'd' for directories, 'l' for symlinks\",\n              \"enum\": [\n                \"f\",\n                \"d\",\n                \"l\"\n              ],\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"required\": [\n            \"pattern\"\n          ],\n          \"type\": \"object\"\n        },\n        \"strict\": false\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"function\",\n      \"function\": {\n        \"name\": \"rg_search\",\n        \"description\": \"Search file contents using ripgrep (rg). Returns matching lines prefixed with their file path and line number. Optionally include N surrounding context lines above and below each match. Omit 'path' to search from the current working directory.\",\n        \"parameters\": {\n          \"additionalProperties\": false,\n          \"properties\": {\n            \"context_lines\": {\n              \"description\": \"Number of lines of context to show around each match (passed as -C to rg)\",\n              \"type\": \"integer\"\n            },\n            \"path\": {\n              \"description\": \"File or directory to search in. Defaults to '.' (current directory)\",\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            },\n            \"pattern\": {\n              \"description\": \"The regex pattern to search for inside file contents\",\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"required\": [\n            \"pattern\"\n          ],\n          \"type\": \"object\"\n        },\n        \"strict\": false\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"stream\": true,\n  \"temperature\": 1.0\n}"
