:### `ui.rs` — Display State Only\\n141:`PromptController`, `ResponseAreaController`, `StatusLineController` own only\\n142:what is needed to render and scroll. They do not hold conversation history.\\n143:Streaming tokens are appended via `add_to_payload`; consecutive tokens of the\\n144:same `MessageKind` are merged to avoid per-token entries.\\n145:\\n146:### `service/commands/` — Slash-Command System\\n147:This module handles user-typed commands (e.g. `/model groq`, `/new`, `/clear`).\\n148:Commands are registered with `CommandController` at startup. The prompt area\\n149:detects a leading `/` and routes input to the command controller instead of the\\n150:LLM. Commands mutate `MessageController` or `App` state directly.\\n151:\\n152:> ⚠\u{fe0f} **Currently incomplete:** `CommandController` stores commands but routing\\n153:> from the prompt is not wired up and `CommandType` variants are unused.\\n154:> Extend this module rather than adding ad-hoc keybindings for meta-operations.\\n155:\\n156:---\\n157:\\n158:## Streaming Architecture\\n159:\\n160:`LLMModel::generate` sends individual `ChatMessageResponse` tokens to a\\n161:`broadcast::Sender<ChatMessageResponse>`. The final chunk carries `done: true`.\\n162:`App` receives these in the `tokio::select!` loop:\\n163:\\n164:1. Non-done content/thinking chunks → forwarded to `ResponseAreaController`\\n165:2. `tool_calls` chunk → `MessageController::set_tool_calls` → `execute_tool` →\\n166:   `set_tool_call_response` → new `generate` spawned to continue the conversation\\n167:3. `done: true` → `MessageController::set_response` records the final assistant turn\\n168:\\n169:Each `generate` call is spawned with `tokio::spawn` making it an independent\\n170:async unit. This is the foundation for future sub-agent and background task\\n171:support — each agent/sub-agent gets its own spawn + channel pair.\\n172:\\n173:---\\n174:\\n175:## Thread Model\\n176:\\n177:`Thread` holds a `Vec<ContextItem>` representing the full conversation history.\\n178:`ContextItem` encodes one turn: system, user, assistant content, tool request,\\n179:or tool response. Use the static constructors (`ContextItem::user`,\\n180:`ContextItem::assistant`, etc.) — never construct the struct directly.\\n181:\\n182:**Future direction:** threads will have a `kind` discriminant:\\n183:- `UserThread` — user-facing, named, switchable via commands\\n184:- `AgentThread` — programmatic, short-lived, used by sub-agents\\n185:\\n186:Keep this in mind when modifying `Thread` or `MessageController`. Do not\\n187:add UI-specific fields to `Thread`.\\n188:\\n189:---\\n190:\\n191:## Configuration & Secrets\\n192:\\n193:API keys are read from environment variables at model construction time:\\n194:- `GROQ_API_KEY` — Groq backend\\n195:\\n196:> ⚠\u{fe0f} **Known violation:** the Groq API key is currently hardcoded in `app.rs`.\\n197:> Move it to `std::env::var(\\\"GROQ_API_KEY\\\")` at the earliest opportunity.\\n198:\\n199:A config file (`~/.config/babak_code/config.toml` or `.data/config.toml`) is\\n200:the right long-term home for model endpoints, default model selection, and\\n201:tool subsets. Do not design new features assuming hardcoded values.\\n202:\\n203:---\\n204:\\n205:## Key Bindings (runtime)\\n206:\\n207:| Key | Action |\\n208:|-----|--------|\\n209:| `Ctrl+P` | Submit prompt |\\n210:| `Enter` | New line in prompt |\\n211:| `Tab` | Toggle focus between Prompt / Response panels |\\n212:| `Ctrl+C` | Quit |\\n213:| `j` / `k` / arrows | Scroll response (when focused) |\\n214:| `Ctrl+D` / `Ctrl+U` | Half-page down / up |\\n215:| `Ctrl+F` / `Ctrl+B` | Full-page down / up |\\n216:| `g` / `G` | Jump to top / bottom |\\n217:\\n218:---\\n219:\\n220:## How to Add a New LLM Backend\\n221:\\n222:1. Create `src/agent/<name>/mod.rs`\\n223:2. Define a struct and implement `LLMModel` via `#[async_trait]`\\n224:3. In `generate`: build the request from `thread` + `tools`, stream the response,\\n225:   send `ChatMessageResponse` tokens to `resp_tx`\\n226:4. Read any API key from an environment variable\\n227:5. Register the model in `app.rs` via `controller.register_model(Arc::new(...))`\\n228:\\n229:Nothing else needs to change. Do not touch `thread.rs`, `tool/`, or `controller.rs`.\\n230:\\n231:---\\n232:\\n233:## How to Add a New Tool\\n234:\\n235:1. Implement the execution function in `tool/file.rs` or `tool/search.rs`\\n236:   (or a new file under `tool/` for a new category)\\n237:2. Define the `Tool` schema (JSON schema parameters) as a public `fn <name>_tool() -> Tool`\\n238:3. Add a match arm in `tool/mod.rs::execute_tool`\\n239:4. Add an entry to `tools_catalog()` in `tool/mod.rs`\\n240:\\n241:The tool is now automatically available to all models (passed via `generate`)\\n242:and described in the system prompt. No changes needed in `agent/` or `controller.rs`.\\n243:\\n244:---\\n245:\\n246:## How to Add a New Slash-Command\\n247:\\n248:1. Define a new variant in `CommandType` (in `service/commands/mod.rs`)\\n249:2. Implement a handler that receives `&mut MessageController` (and/or `&mut App`)\\n250:3. Register it in `app.rs` via `command_controller.add_command(...)`\\n251:4. The prompt routing (detect `/`, parse command name + args, dispatch) is\\n252:   in `PromptController::handle_event` — wire it there\\n253:\\n254:---\\n255:\\n256:## Tests\\n257:\\n258:Unit tests are not required during active development. The `components/prompt_dialog.rs`\\n259:module contains tests for the dialog widget — keep them passing.\\n260:When the architecture stabilises, tests belong closest to the logic they cover\\n261:(inline `#[cfg(test)]` modules), not in a separate `tests/` tree.\\n262:\\n263:---\\n264:\\n265:## What Not To Do\\n266:\\n267:- **Do not add logic to `models/`** — it is a data contract layer only\\n268:- **Do not hardcode model names or tool lists outside `agent/`**\\n269:- **Do not add conversation state to `ui.rs`** — display state only\\n270:- **Do not add ad-hoc keybindings for meta-operations** — use the commands module\\n271:- **Do not copy the `Into<UserChatMessageRequest>` pattern from `thread.rs`** — it is a known violation scheduled for removal\\n272:- **Do not discuss architectural changes inline in code** — raise them before implementing\\n\",\n      \"tool_call_id\": \"fc_88e45815-0f30-4230-ac9b-834f08cc4e64\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"tools\": [\n    {\n      \"type\": \"function\",\n      \"function\": {\n        \"name\": \"read_file\",\n        \"description\": \"partial file read based on line_from and line_to parameters. keep line_to rather small number so that parts of file needed is fetched. if line_to is greater than file lines, line_from to end of file is returned\",\n        \"parameters\": {\n          \"additionalProperties\": false,\n          \"properties\": {\n            \"line_from\": {\n              \"description\": \"Starting line number to read from\",\n              \"type\": \"integer\"\n            },\n            \"line_to\": {\n              \"description\": \"Ending line number to read to.\",\n              \"type\": \"integer\"\n            },\n            \"path\": {\n              \"description\": \"Path to the file to read\",\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"required\": [\n            \"path\",\n            \"line_from\",\n            \"line_to\"\n          ],\n          \"type\": \"object\"\n        },\n        \"strict\": true\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"function\",\n      \"function\": {\n        \"name\": \"list_files_and_directories\",\n        \"description\": \"List all files and directories in a given directory. directories are shown with \\\"\\\\\\\" at the end of name\",\n        \"parameters\": {\n          \"additionalProperties\": false,\n          \"properties\": {\n            \"path\": {\n              \"description\": \"Path to the directory to list files from\",\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"required\": [\n            \"path\"\n          ],\n          \"type\": \"object\"\n        },\n        \"strict\": true\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"function\",\n      \"function\": {\n        \"name\": \"create_file\",\n        \"description\": \"Create a new file at the given path with the provided content. Parent directories are created automatically if they do not exist. Overwrites the file if it already exists.\",\n        \"parameters\": {\n          \"additionalProperties\": false,\n          \"properties\": {\n            \"content\": {\n              \"description\": \"Full text content to write into the file\",\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            },\n            \"path\": {\n              \"description\": \"Path of the file to create\",\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"required\": [\n            \"path\",\n            \"content\"\n          ],\n          \"type\": \"object\"\n        },\n        \"strict\": true\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"function\",\n      \"function\": {\n        \"name\": \"edit_file\",\n        \"description\": \"Edit an existing file by replacing an exact occurrence of old_text with new_text. old_text must match exactly once in the file — the call fails if it is not found or appears more than once. Use read_file first to obtain the exact text to match.\",\n        \"parameters\": {\n          \"additionalProperties\": false,\n          \"properties\": {\n            \"new_text\": {\n              \"description\": \"Text to replace old_text with\",\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            },\n            \"old_text\": {\n              \"description\": \"Exact text to search for in the file. Must appear exactly once.\",\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            },\n            \"path\": {\n              \"description\": \"Path to the file to edit\",\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"required\": [\n            \"path\",\n            \"old_text\",\n            \"new_text\"\n          ],\n          \"type\": \"object\"\n        },\n        \"strict\": true\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"function\",\n      \"function\": {\n        \"name\": \"fd_search\",\n        \"description\": \"Search for files and directories by name using fd (fd-find). Returns matching paths one per line. Use 'type' to filter: 'f' = files only, 'd' = directories only, 'l' = symlinks only. Omit 'type' to match all entry kinds. Omit 'path' to search from the current working directory.\",\n        \"parameters\": {\n          \"additionalProperties\": false,\n          \"properties\": {\n            \"path\": {\n              \"description\": \"Root directory to search in. Defaults to '.' (current directory)\",\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            },\n            \"pattern\": {\n              \"description\": \"The name pattern to search for (regex)\",\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            },\n            \"type\": {\n              \"description\": \"Entry type filter: 'f' for files, 'd' for directories, 'l' for symlinks\",\n              \"enum\": [\n                \"f\",\n                \"d\",\n                \"l\"\n              ],\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"required\": [\n            \"pattern\"\n          ],\n          \"type\": \"object\"\n        },\n        \"strict\": false\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"function\",\n      \"function\": {\n        \"name\": \"rg_search\",\n        \"description\": \"Search file contents using ripgrep (rg). Returns matching lines prefixed with their file path and line number. Optionally include N surrounding context lines above and below each match. Omit 'path' to search from the current working directory.\",\n        \"parameters\": {\n          \"additionalProperties\": false,\n          \"properties\": {\n            \"context_lines\": {\n              \"description\": \"Number of lines of context to show around each match (passed as -C to rg)\",\n              \"type\": \"integer\"\n            },\n            \"path\": {\n              \"description\": \"File or directory to search in. Defaults to '.' (current directory)\",\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            },\n            \"pattern\": {\n              \"description\": \"The regex pattern to search for inside file contents\",\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"required\": [\n            \"pattern\"\n          ],\n          \"type\": \"object\"\n        },\n        \"strict\": false\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"stream\": true,\n  \"temperature\": 1.0\n}"
